{"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":3,"patch":0},"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/org.liuliu.s4nnc\/documentation\/NNC\/ModelBuilder"},"relationshipsSections":[{"kind":"relationships","identifiers":["doc:\/\/org.liuliu.s4nnc\/documentation\/NNC\/AnyModelBuilder"],"title":"Inherits From","type":"inheritsFrom"},{"kind":"relationships","identifiers":["doc:\/\/org.liuliu.s4nnc\/documentation\/NNC\/AnyModel"],"title":"Conforms To","type":"conformsTo"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"A model builder is a more generic type of model. A model can be quite static,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"thus, you have to be quite careful to have a model work with dynamic inputs."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"You cannot use reshape, or anything that can generate fixed tensor outputs from"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"a fixed inputs."}],"kind":"symbol","primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"final"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"class"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"ModelBuilder"},{"kind":"text","text":"<"},{"kind":"genericParameter","text":"T"},{"kind":"text","text":">"}],"platforms":["Linux"],"languages":["swift"]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"text":"Overview","type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"overview"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A model builder on the other hand doesn’t have that restriction. When input changes,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"it simply calls the given builder closure to construct a new model. In such way,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"you can continue to use reshape etc to assume fixed inputs and outputs, it will just"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"work for dynamic inputs. The newly built model will carry over stateful components"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"(parameters) from the old models, thus, it doesn’t reset your training. This also means"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"you need to make sure parameter shape won’t change when input changes, otherwise we"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"will fatal."}]}]}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/org.liuliu.s4nnc\/documentation\/NNC"]]},"metadata":{"navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"ModelBuilder"}],"roleHeading":"Class","title":"ModelBuilder","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"class"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"ModelBuilder"}],"role":"symbol","symbolKind":"class","modules":[{"name":"NNC"}],"externalID":"s:3NNC12ModelBuilderC"},"sections":[],"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/nnc\/modelbuilder"]}],"topicSections":[{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/org.liuliu.s4nnc\/documentation\/NNC\/ModelBuilder\/init(_:name:)-4pup0","doc:\/\/org.liuliu.s4nnc\/documentation\/NNC\/ModelBuilder\/init(_:name:)-55gex"],"title":"Initializers"},{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/org.liuliu.s4nnc\/documentation\/NNC\/ModelBuilder\/callAsFunction(_:inputs:_:streamContext:)-101bg","doc:\/\/org.liuliu.s4nnc\/documentation\/NNC\/ModelBuilder\/callAsFunction(_:inputs:_:streamContext:)-4i10p","doc:\/\/org.liuliu.s4nnc\/documentation\/NNC\/ModelBuilder\/callAsFunction(inputs:_:streamContext:)-4tnis","doc:\/\/org.liuliu.s4nnc\/documentation\/NNC\/ModelBuilder\/callAsFunction(inputs:_:streamContext:)-8pae9","doc:\/\/org.liuliu.s4nnc\/documentation\/NNC\/ModelBuilder\/compile(_:inputs:isEager:)-1lsvw","doc:\/\/org.liuliu.s4nnc\/documentation\/NNC\/ModelBuilder\/compile(_:inputs:isEager:)-8ge5z","doc:\/\/org.liuliu.s4nnc\/documentation\/NNC\/ModelBuilder\/compile(inputs:isEager:)-4kat6","doc:\/\/org.liuliu.s4nnc\/documentation\/NNC\/ModelBuilder\/compile(inputs:isEager:)-4yweq"],"title":"Instance Methods"}],"references":{"doc://org.liuliu.s4nnc/documentation/NNC/ModelBuilder":{"navi